title: The Verdict
overview: A lawyer sees the chance to salvage his career and self-respect by taking a medical malpractice case to trial rather than settling.

title: The Lunchbox
overview: A mistaken delivery in Mumbai's famously efficient lunchbox delivery system connects a young housewife to an older man in the dusk of his life as they build a fantasy world together through notes in the lunchbox.

title: The Wrestler
overview: A faded professional wrestler must retire, but finds his quest for a new life outside the ring a dispiriting struggle.

title: The Color Purple
overview: A black Southern woman struggles to find her identity after suffering abuse from her father and others over four decades.

title: The Help
overview: An aspiring author during the civil rights movement of the 1960s decides to write a book detailing the African American maids' point of view on the white families for which they work, and the hardships they go through on a daily basis.

title: The Notebook
overview: A poor yet passionate young man falls in love with a rich young woman, giving her a sense of freedom, but they are soon separated because of their social differences.

title: The Florida Project
overview: Set over one summer, the film follows precocious six-year-old Moonee as she courts mischief and adventure with her ragtag playmates and bonds with her rebellious but caring mother, all while living in the shadows of Walt Disney World.

title: The Prestige
overview: After a tragic accident, two stage magicians engage in a battle to create the ultimate illusion while sacrificing everything they have to outwit each other.

title: The Machinist
overview: An industrial worker who hasn't slept in a year begins to doubt his own sanity.

title: The Shining
overview: A family heads to an isolated hotel for the winter where a sinister presence influences the father into violence, while his psychic son sees horrific forebodings from both past and future.

title: The Grapes of Wrath
overview: A poor Midwest family is forced off their land. They travel to California, suffering the misfortunes of the homeless in the Great Depression.

title: Midnight Cowboy
overview: A naive hustler travels from Texas to New York City to seek personal fortune, finding a new friend in the process.

title: The Manchurian Candidate
overview: A former prisoner of war is brainwashed as an unwitting assassin for an international Communist conspiracy.

title: The Magdalene Sisters
overview: Three young Irish women struggle to maintain their spirits while they endure dehumanizing abuse as inmates of a Magdalene Sisters Asylum.

title: The Birds
overview: A wealthy San Francisco socialite pursues a potential boyfriend to a small Northern California town that slowly takes a turn for the bizarre when birds of all kinds suddenly begin to attack people.

title: The Shawshank Redemption
overview: Two imprisoned men bond over a number of years, finding solace and eventual redemption through acts of common decency.

title: The Hustler
overview: An up-and-coming pool player plays a long-time champion in a single high-stakes match.

title: The Man Who Shot Liberty Valance
overview: A senator returns to a western town for the funeral of an old friend and tells the story of his origins.

title: Kis Uykusu
overview: A hotel owner and landlord in a remote Turkish village deals with conflicts within his family and a tenant behind on his rent.

title: The Butterfly Effect
overview: Evan Treborn suffers blackouts during significant events of his life. As he grows up, he finds a way to remember these lost memories and a supernatural way to alter his life by reading his journal.
